        <body><div type="bibliography">
                
            <p>Not published before <bibl><ptr target="#IGCyr"/> <citedRange>119800</citedRange></bibl>.</p>
            </div><div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">
                
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"><certainty locus="name" match=".."/></gap> <persName type="divine" ref="#Apollo"><name nymRef="#Ἀπόλλων"><seg part="I"><supplied reason="lost">Ἀπόλ</supplied>λων</seg><gap reason="lost" atLeast="1" atMost="2" unit="character"/></name></persName> <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"><certainty locus="name" match=".."/></gap>
                </ab>
            </div><div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
            
                <p/>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="fr" xml:space="preserve">
            <p><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> de/à Apollon <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="en" xml:space="preserve">
            <p><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> of/for Apollon <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="it" xml:space="preserve">
            <p><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> di/per Apollo <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>.</p>
            </div><div type="commentary">
                
                <p>The name of the god is certain, but it cannot be decided whether it was here at the genitive or at the dative case.</p>
                <p>This fragment appears on a photograph (not numbered) from the Department archive very plausibly earlier than World War II, where it stood alongside with 
                    <ref type="inscription" source="#IGCyr2">IGCyr120300</ref>.</p>
	       <p/>
	<p/>
            </div></body>
